results.name: Square array A(row,col): A(row,1) = A276937(row), and for col > 1, A(row,col) = A003961(A(row,col-1)), read by descending antidiagonals: A(1,1), A(1,2), A(2,1), A(1,3), A(2,2), A(3,1), etc.
comment: The starting offset is 2 because 1 is not included in the array proper. With it the terms are a permutation of A276078.
All terms on each row have the same prime signature.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..631; the first 35 antidiagonals of array
